+  // Keyboard avoidance. This gate is a bottom-anchored (`items-end`) fixed
+  // sheet. On iOS WebKit a `position:fixed` element is NOT moved when the soft
+  // keyboard opens (it stays pinned to the layout-viewport bottom, i.e. behind
+  // the keyboard), and Capacitor is configured `Keyboard.resize:'none'` so the
+  // OS gives us no avoidance either - the app owns it via `--kb-height`. Without
+  // lifting the sheet, focusing the field raises the keyboard on top of both the
+  // input and the "Save and continue" button: the user cannot see what they type
+  // and cannot reach Save, so signup dead-ends. This is the exact class of bug
+  // the shared BottomSheet already solves with `bottom: keyboardHeight` (added
+  // after the 2026-04-29 "Save button behind keyboard" report). PhoneGate never
+  // adopted BottomSheet, so it reproduced the same defect on the signup path.
+  // Fix: pad the flex container by the live keyboard height so `items-end`
+  // parks the sheet flush on top of the keyboard, fully visible.
+  const keyboardHeight = useKeyboardHeight()
+
